108  NSVec4<T> & axisAngleFrom(const nsquat<T> & orientation, bool rads = false)
109  {
110  // http://www.euclideanspace.com/maths/geometry/rotations/conversions/quaternionToAngle/index.htm
111  w = static_cast<T>(2 * std::acos(orientation.w));
112 
113  if (!rads)
114  w = degrees(w);
115 
116  T den = static_cast<T>(std::sqrt(1 - orientation.w*orientation.w));
117  if (den < EPS)
118  {
119  x = orientation.x;
120  y = orientation.y;
121  z = orientation.z;
122  }
123  else
124  {
125  x = orientation.x / den;
126  y = orientation.y / den;
127  z = orientation.z / den;
128  }
129  return *this;
130  }

210  template<class T2 >
211  NSVec4<T> & lerp(const NSVec4<T> & vec, const T2 & scalingFactor)
212  {
213  x += static_cast<T>((vec.x - x)*scalingFactor);
214  y += static_cast<T>((vec.y - y)*scalingFactor);
215  z += static_cast<T>((vec.z - z)*scalingFactor);
216  w += static_cast<T>((vec.w - w)*scalingFactor);
217  return *this;
218  }

292  NSVec3<T> & scalingFrom(const nsmat3<T> & transform)
293  {

297  w = static_cast<T>(1);

300 
301  NSVec3<T> & scalingFrom(const nsmat4<T> & transform)
302  {
303  x = sqrt(transform[0][0] * transform[0][0] + transform[0][1] * transform[0][1] + transform[0][2] * transform[0][2]);
304  y = sqrt(transform[1][0] * transform[1][0] + transform[1][1] * transform[1][1] + transform[1][2] * transform[1][2]);
305  z = sqrt(transform[2][0] * transform[2][0] + transform[2][1] * transform[2][1] + transform[2][2] * transform[2][2]);
306  w = static_cast<T>(1);
307  return *this;
308  }
